author: George Wilson
title: Dolphin retrieves Miami Heat Dancer's phone from ocean
text:
Dolphin retrieves Miami Heat Dancer's phone from ocean Video: Dolphin fetches Heat dancer's phone from ocean floor 
Finally! A win for the Dolphins! Fortunately for Heat dancer Teresa Cee, it was an ocean-going dolphin -- and not the football Dolphins -- that helped her when her cell phone was inadvertently dropped in the ocean off the Bahamas recently.

George Wilson Contact Reporter South Florida Sun Sentinel A dolphin, one that lives in the sea, came to the rescue of an overboard cellphone of a Miami Heat dancer 
Finally! A win for the Dolphins! Fortunately for Miami Heat dancer Teresa Cee, it was an ocean-going dolphin and not a Miami Dolphins player ---given the team's recent performance -- that made the assist when she lost her cellphone. 
Cee's cellphone went overboard into the ocean off the Bahamas during a recent excursion to shoot the Heat Dancers' annual calendar. 
Cacique, a dolphin who was entertaining the dancers, apparently spotted the phone on the ocean floor and fetched it for Cee, who was said to be "tickled" by the happy outcome. 
The resulting video has blown up on social media and resulted in a flood of phone calls from news organizations seeking comment from the Miami Heat. 
While Cee is amazed how one little incident went viral, it’s easy to see how popular the short video has become: Take one dancer, add bikini and a smart, loveable dolphin and you’ve got online gold…and one drowned cellphone.
